article.headline: Colorado 71, Fresno St. 64
article.story: BOULDER, Colo. -- Andre Roberson had a career-high 21 points and 10 rebounds, Spencer Dinwiddie scored 15 points and Colorado beat Fresno State 71-64 on Wednesday night. Austin Dufault had 13 points for the Buffaloes (5-3), who have won 27 straight against nonconference opponents at home. Kevin Olekaibe led Fresno State (4-5) with 26 points. Colorado led 38-23 at halftime before Fresno State rallied. Olekaibe had 17 of his points after the break as the Bulldogs pulled to within three. They had a chance to tie, but Tyler Johnson's 3-pointer with 4:26 left rimmed out. Roberson came into the game averaging 9.7 points. He had 13 by halftime.
